In May 2011, Alexis Fleisig was asked to temporarily fill the spot left by Scott Gursky for the band Obits.
Originally just a touring member, Flesig recorded the group's third album, titled Bed & Bugs, in 2013.
Known primarily for his involvement in the post-hardcore group Girls Against Boys, Fleisig was also a founding member of the Soulside and currently performs in Paramount Styles and Bellini.
